text:
I don't think anyone else has brought this up yet, if they have sorry, but i figured i would mention it ... 
I know your specs are top tier, so unless some really "funny" stuff is going on in the background your pc shouldn't be having any issues, that beings said since it sounds like you bought a prebuilt, it possible that one or both of the following is true, 1, it has "bloatware" basicly a bunch of stuff running in the background that bogs your computer down, or 2, it is thermal throttling, basicly the components are running too near their thermal limits that they start running slower to try and not be pushed past their thermal limits to protect themselves ... the first can usually be solved with a clean install of windows (or whatever OS you are using), it'll take some time and prob be a bit stressful, but you might not have to, ask your managers and genmates before this one i recommend ... the second one can be solved with new fans, a new case, and/or a new place for your PC basicly its not getting enough "cool" air to keep the components cool, so you can try moving it out into the open more, a choked off cubby is generally the cause of this part, sometimes the fans just aren't sufficient enough for the components you have, if there are only a couple fans, this might solve the issue right away cause you need fans to move air from outside the case to inside it, and then back out again ... lastly, the case itself could be the issue, not all cases are created equal, and some are just significantly more choked for air than others, easy tells for this one are limited places to put fans, a front panel that is a solid materal with little to no holes, and generally a cramped case


Regardless of whether you read and potentially take my comment to mind know that we love you Gura even though all the scuff, i just want you to have a good time : )
